---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Methodology · kpop-mv-data">
  <header class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
    <h1>How public data is collected</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Snapshots come from YouTube Data API <code>videos.list</code>. This project
      stores public counters only. Derived promotion metrics are out of scope for
      the public surface.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Cadence</h2>
    <ul class="plain">
      <li>0–72h after publish → every 10 minutes</li>
      <li>Day 4–14 → hourly</li>
      <li>Day 15–90 → every 6 hours</li>
      <li>90+ days → daily</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Public fields</h2>
    <ul class="plain">
      <li><code>video_id</code>, <code>channel_id</code></li>
      <li><code>snapshot_at</code>, <code>view_count</code>, <code>like_count</code>, <code>comment_count</code></li>
      <li><code>data_source</code>, <code>collector_version</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="note">
    <h2>Not published here</h2>
    <p>
      Charts-unrecognized estimates, organic/non-organic labels, and promotion
      leaderboards stay in a private analysis project that only reads these
      snapshots.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
